			<ns0:name>bradnelson@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/bradnelson@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently, large sections of NaCl's scons side build really should be in the Chrome repo.
Eventually these will likely be moved to gyp + other test harnesses.
However, as an incremental step, we should divide the scons build in half.
We should physically divide SConstruct into two separate files that will eventually live in the two repos.
A command line flag should test each configuration and we should run them separately on native client's buildbots.
Once the build is divided, SCons should be able to tell us which files need to reside on each side, and which files are shared.
